Defendant Lydell L Nichols in court with attorney Scott P. Phillips.  Defendant Lydell L Nichols in custody.  Benjamin Lindsay appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.  Filed, Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense, Sherri N., and defendant. 
 
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 6 YEARS, CONSECUTIVE to any other time being served with credit for 194 days served. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 3 1/2 YEARS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 2 1/2 YEARS.

The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program AFTER SERVING 2 1/2 YEARS OF THIS SENTENCE.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED/SUPERVISION:
*Obtain Mental assessment and if necessary successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*Take any prescription medication only in the manner/dosage as prescribed by a treating physician;
*Obtain AODA assessment and successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzer tests;
*No drug dealing or association with drug community (drug users/dealers or drug houses);
*Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*No contact with victims Kristina R., Katherine G., Kristine B., and Marine Bank located at 333 N. 35th St., Milwaukee;
*Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school and part time employment;
*Participate in Cognitive Thinking program;
*Obtain GED or HSED;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs; 

State in compliance with victim rights legislation.  The Court ordered restitution set at zero.  The Court ordered that all financial obligations be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.  Appeal rights given.
